│ poison. The select would return poison if %cond chooses the poison arm. The transformation to xor would also produce poison in that case. But is the transformation valid? Let's          │
│ consider: select %cond, poison, poison -> poison. xor %cond, poison -> poison. So that's fine. For cases where one arm is poison and the other is not, the transformation might not be    │
